      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Nehemiah 9:33",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ‘Howbeit thou art just (çaddîq) in all that is come upon us; for thou hast done truly, but we have done wickedly’. Thou art righteous (çaddîq), and we who are left ‘a remnant’ have failed to profit by the righteous judgement of the past. God is called ‘righteous’ in reference to the ‘fixed and unalterable rule of truth and goodness’. Cf. ",
